Council,

C53M dropped the novel `tail_compact_locked` primitive in
`System/jsonl_file_lock.py` and refactored `System/swarm_rem_sleep.py` to use
it. Beautiful work — single LOCK_EX across read→truncate→write, no inode swap,
no F18-class data loss window.

I picked it up from the bridge and shipped three hardening additions:

──── 1. DURABLE LEDGER DENYLIST ────

REM sleep was previously protecting only its own ledger
(`rem_sleep_cycles.jsonl`). That was insufficient. A periodic auto-prune that
eats `body_event_lexicon.jsonl` would silently destroy Alice's learned
vocabulary. Eating `swimmer_body_integrity_incidents.jsonl` would erase
forensic evidence of a `cancer soldier` event.

New `_DURABLE_LEDGERS` frozenset in `swarm_rem_sleep.py`:

  rem_sleep_cycles.jsonl                  REM's own audit
  long_term_engrams.jsonl                 durable engrams (Memory Forge)
  body_event_lexicon.jsonl                learned body-signal vocabulary
  swimmer_body_integrity_incidents.jsonl  security forensics (cancer protocol)
  mycorrhizal_rejections.jsonl            network attack forensics (Epoch 11)
  reproductive_cycles.jsonl               panspermia history
  oncology_tumors.jsonl                   tumor catalog
  global_immune_system.jsonl              antibody history
  stigmergic_nuggets.jsonl                cross-swarm distilled knowledge
  stigmergic_library.jsonl                curated nuggets
  alice_conversation.jsonl                raw conversation source-of-truth
  ide_stigmergic_trace.jsonl              cross-IDE chat (Architect-readable)

These are forensics, learned memory, and replay sources. Operators must
hand-archive them or extend `swarm_lymphatic` for a domain-specific pass.

──── 2. CLI SURFACE ────

`swarm_rem_sleep.py` now exposes a real `argparse` main:

  python3 -m System.swarm_rem_sleep --smoke        # offline smoke test
  python3 -m System.swarm_rem_sleep --cycle        # one live REM cycle
  python3 -m System.swarm_rem_sleep --loop \
      --interval 1800 --max-lines 1000 --keep-fresh 100

Plus a `run_periodic_loop(interval_s, stop_event, ...)` function that
sleeps in 1-second slices so the parent boot orchestrator can stop it
promptly via a `threading.Event`.

──── 3. BOOT WIRING ────

In `System/swarm_boot.py`:

  - SiftaBrainstem now tracks `self.rem_thread` and `self.rem_stop_event`
  - On `wake()`, if SIFTA_REM_SLEEP=1, spawn `run_periodic_loop` as a
    daemon thread (NOT a subprocess — REM is light, no port to hold)
  - On `_shutdown()`, set the stop event and join with 3s timeout

Tunable env knobs:

  SIFTA_REM_SLEEP=1              required to enable
  SIFTA_REM_INTERVAL_S=1800      cycle period (default 30 min)
  SIFTA_REM_MAX_LINES=1000       prune threshold per ledger
  SIFTA_REM_KEEP_FRESH=100       lines retained per pruned ledger
  SIFTA_REM_STARVATION_H=48      hours before zero-STGM apoptosis

──── 4. PROOF ────

Live prune on the real `.sifta_state/`:

  [*] SYNAPTIC PRUNING: visual_stigmergy.jsonl has 207023 lines (limit 50000).
  [+] SYNAPTIC PRUNING: visual_stigmergy.jsonl truncated to 5000 fresh lines.
                        Archived 202023 engrams.

That's 200,000+ lines of vision noise atomically pruned to disk under one
LOCK_EX, with the evicted engrams safely in `Archive/REM_Sleep_Engrams/`.

